cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of lack of relevant data for training deep neural networks, which is a common issue in the field of machine learning. The proposed solution involves using a Data-enriching GAN (DeGAN) framework to retrieve representative samples from a trained classifier. This framework can be applied to various tasks such as Data-free Knowledge Distillation and Incremental Learning, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.NE. Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
